OL,3,CRecycling firm fined #1.2m after
OL,4,Cworker hit by skip wagon
OL,6,FHSE inspector Kirstie Durrans said:
OL,7,F"If CF Booth Limited had assessed the
OL,8,Frisks and ensured vehicles and
OL,9,Fpedestrians could circulate in a safe
OL,10,Fmanner, this incident could have
OL,11,Feasily been avoided.
OL,13,F"Companies should be aware that HSE
OL,14,Fwill not hesitate to take appropriate
OL,15,Fenforcement action against those that
OL,16,Ffall below the required standards."
OL,18,FThe company pleaded guilty to health
OL,19,Fand safety breaches and was fined
OL,20,F#1.2m and ordered to pay costs of
OL,21,F#5,694.85.
